Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.45,0:00:27.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hold those guys off until I get the engine lockout disengaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.87,0:00:28.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.18,0:00:35.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Von Braun will reach the point of no return in 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.78,0:00:37.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When she passes that point,\N she won't be able to recover her orbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.14,0:00:38.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What about the patrol ships?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.29,0:00:41.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're in transit!\NETA is 47 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.79,0:00:43.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why are they even bothering, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.51,0:00:45.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If the Von Braun crashes onto\NSea of Tranquility City,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.60,0:00:49.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...its 120,000 residents will all be wiped out in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.51,0:00:53.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Space development will be dealt a massive setback.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.14,0:00:59.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come, let's bear witness together. Let's watch as the course of history is changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.65,0:02:34.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've been told that you've received warning after warning from the Space Defense Front!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.67,0:02:37.84,F.O. (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(590,372,420,365)\fad(760,830)\bord0.1\shad2\fs20\fscx100\fscy100\t(\fs28\fscx100\fscy100)}Love
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.42,0:02:36.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's because we're fast-tracking the Chairman's bill!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.17,0:02:37.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that we should give in to the terrorists?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.63,0:02:40.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's so bad about the people who kick in the most money getting concessions in return?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.46,0:02:40.03,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.28,0:02:43.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've received word that your son\N Colin-sama is aboard the Von Braun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.69,0:02:45.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't waste my time with that nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.89,0:02:49.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The children I had by Milly are nothing but spares.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.10,0:02:58.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No way am I going to die here!\NI haven't bled the old man dry yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:01.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it's all right for us to escape by ourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.98,0:03:06.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a problem. As long as I survive, the Von Braun can be rebuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.96,0:03:10.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, she's my precious baby, so I plan to wait until the last minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.21,0:03:15.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We meet again. You have no idea how happy this makes me, Hakim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.06,0:03:19.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was sure that you'd come.\NI knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.85,0:03:23.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk to me about determination if you can't back it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.45,0:03:30.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I am gonna back it up.\NThis time, I'm ready to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.12,0:03:35.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Got it! Yuri, we're gonna light up the ME before they can stop us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.01,0:03:37.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.02,0:03:39.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna use the Toy Box to nudge the Von Braun upwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.08,0:03:41.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But there's too much mass to...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.40,0:03:44.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know the Toy Box can't do it by herself. But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.32,0:03:46.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head for the point of no return!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.84,0:03:47.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.96,0:03:51.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we fly at top speed on a parabolic orbit, we'll end up right beneath the Von Braun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.01,0:03:52.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And do what when we get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.32,0:03:54.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the comm interference,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.37,0:03:57.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...we should assume that something's happened to the Von Braun!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.11,0:03:59.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Someone has to get confirmation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.83,0:04:02.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And if it comes down to it, we'll use this to shove her back into lunar orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.12,0:04:05.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Push the Von Braun?!\NWith this one ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.76,0:04:07.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If other ships come, we might be able to manage!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.36,0:04:11.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What if we go and no one else is there?\NWe won't be able to call for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.64,0:04:14.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Whether or not anybody else goes doesn't matter to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.29,0:04:18.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's right... I can't just sit here and do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:21.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi's on that ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:29.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are they dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.26,0:04:34.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,B-But if somebody's alive, I have to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.97,0:04:40.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can still...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.93,0:04:44.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire-san?! What are you doing on the Von Braun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.37,0:04:45.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.82,0:04:57.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you... doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.46,0:04:58.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire-san! Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.49,0:05:03.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad... I have to find an escape capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.36,0:05:09.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I take it that you can see the Von Braun falling from where you are, gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:13.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is it clear to you now that\NI am a man of my word?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.45,0:05:18.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Space development is vital for humanity.\NWe have no intention of stopping now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.29,0:05:24.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"We"? It's a shame that when you say "we," you aren't including all of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:27.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, I will issue my demands now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:28.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your demands?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.90,0:05:30.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.60,0:05:34.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a simple matter. Reject the bill that the chairman is proposing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:40.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The notion that the bounty of space can be monopolized by the few is a terrible thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.38,0:05:52.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're one of Gigalt Sensei's students, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.28,0:05:54.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can make quick decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.73,0:05:57.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And who's the one who betrayed him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.51,0:06:00.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I had the utmost respect for Sensei.\NBut even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.30,0:06:01.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cut the crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.68,0:06:03.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's no good, now you're being reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:05.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You fanatic!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.57,0:06:13.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who's the fanatic.\NYou're obsessed with space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.71,0:06:15.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I do what I do because\NI have an objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.02,0:06:18.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To do what?! Destroy a whole damn city?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.63,0:06:21.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The population of Sea of Tranquility City is only 120,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.87,0:06:22.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Only"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:26.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino, do you know how many people starved to death last year?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.00,0:06:27.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that got to...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:29.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Five million people!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.07,0:06:32.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ten million people died from diseases that they could have been vaccinated against.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.56,0:06:36.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And 850,000 people have died in Mananga's civil war!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.95,0:06:39.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is one life worth more than another?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.26,0:06:43.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The lives down there in that city were bought at the expense of countless deaths!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.99,0:06:48.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that our lives mean nothing?\NThat only yours are precious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.12,0:06:50.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.07,0:06:58.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're Chairman Clifford's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:07:01.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, that's right. I'm INTO inspector\NColin Clifford.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.68,0:07:03.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Escort us to a safe location.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.27,0:07:04.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. Up ahead, there's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.68,0:07:10.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Colin-san, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.71,0:07:13.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.16,0:07:17.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.68,0:07:22.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's all over! Mother, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.80,0:07:24.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I never... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.22,0:07:25.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.83,0:07:29.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I still have a lot of things that I want to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.62,0:07:31.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Clothes that I want to own!\NPlaces that I want to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.97,0:07:33.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And all kinds of foods that I want to try!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.04,0:07:38.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.03,0:07:40.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.63,0:07:41.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hide in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.59,0:07:43.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find you a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.78,0:07:48.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We lost pressure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.32,0:07:50.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like they've isolated the entire block.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:53.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.65,0:07:56.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do any good here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:08:00.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai... We'll see each other again, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.62,0:08:05.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once we reach the hull, latch on with the arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.03,0:08:06.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.87,0:08:10.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're really on a direct course for\NSea of Tranquility City, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.17,0:08:15.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See, what did I tell you?\NNobody else came!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.22,0:08:17.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but the Von Braun is definitely falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.25,0:08:19.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try to nudge their trajectory upwards!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.72,0:08:21.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Moron, think about their mass!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.64,0:08:23.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably too late to keep her from crashing,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.82,0:08:27.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but I want to at least prevent a direct hit, even by a little!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.49,0:08:32.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've gotta change their trajectory, just a little!\NTo somewhere that's unpopulated!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.03,0:08:36.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They should reach the point of no return any moment now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:39.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Victory is ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.81,0:08:42.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity came into space too soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.99,0:08:45.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're going. We can't wait any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:47.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use, it's too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.63,0:08:48.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a direct hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.96,0:08:59.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1300)}Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:05.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The engine's started up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.73,0:09:12.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Von Braun, she's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.62,0:09:16.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's climbing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:23.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The INTO Supreme Council has rejected the\NChairman's bill, which proposed that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.32,0:09:26.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...lunar resources be distributed according to member contributions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.65,0:09:30.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...announcing instead that a distribution system based on population would be adopted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.91,0:09:34.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This unprecedented announcement on the first day of the meeting...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.35,0:09:36.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...runs completely counter to the outcome that was expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.64,0:09:39.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All parties involved are unable to conceal their surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.40,0:09:43.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've contacted your sponsor and have received confirmation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.79,0:09:46.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We said we will relinquish territorial rights to the island in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.65,0:09:50.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're a tough man. You brokered a deal in front of 120,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.42,0:09:54.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's what they mean by\N "With power comes responsibility."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.75,0:10:00.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now that the engines are back online,\NI suppose we can call off our great escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:01.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.80,0:10:06.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is that a deal has been struck between INTO and the Space Defense Front.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.24,0:10:12.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this war began behind the scenes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:16.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and that's where this war ended, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.47,0:10:22.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've been abandoned?\NI can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:29.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Always staying on the move, always trying to see what's over the next horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:31.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that isn't the proper path for humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.11,0:10:35.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late to hit the brakes now...\NWe're already on the move!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.29,0:10:39.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Climb the mountain because it's there," is that what you're saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.55,0:10:41.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.07,0:10:46.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can never rest until you've conquered everything? You won't be satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.34,0:10:48.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity has to know its limitations!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.28,0:10:52.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, pal, but that's one word that I can't stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.93,0:11:10.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's more like it.\NThose are the eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.73,0:11:13.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The eyes of a man who's capable of eliminating anything in his way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.05,0:11:15.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...with as much emotion as swatting a fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.31,0:11:20.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you pull that trigger, you'll be a whole new man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.09,0:11:24.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be reborn as an animal who can only move ahead. One whose brakes are broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.99,0:11:29.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going up against the universe itself.\NThat suits me just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.25,0:11:32.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then go ahead and shoot.\NAnd fall into the abyss.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.24,0:11:37.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And realize that your relationships with Gigalt Sensei and me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.82,0:11:40.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...were just passing associations that meant nothing to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.26,0:11:42.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I'll shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.93,0:11:49.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll shoot you, and then I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.72,0:12:05.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Claire-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.48,0:12:09.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The capsule is sending out an automatic SOS signal,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.97,0:12:12.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so a rescue team from Sea of Tranquility\NCity should be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.29,0:12:16.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Long-range communications are out...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.83,0:12:20.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,SOS! Do you read me?!\NOrbital Security Agency!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.53,0:12:26.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?\NIt's 1200km to the city...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.18,0:12:28.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this might work!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.43,0:12:29.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:35.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be in trouble if we stay here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.49,0:12:40.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we sit still, our air tanks will run dry in ten hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.71,0:12:43.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I sent out an SOS, but there's no telling if it was picked up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.84,0:12:51.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that a ship spots us from orbit, but if we're gonna increase our chances of survival,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.78,0:12:54.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...we have to get moving, and get moving right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.80,0:13:03.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't open a channel on our regular frequency yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.20,0:13:05.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maintain radio silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.96,0:13:08.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's a chance that the Space Defense\NFront will use them against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.26,0:13:14.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, not the Space Defense Front again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.99,0:13:17.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dolf! Hang in there, Dolf!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.73,0:13:19.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Show us your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.46,0:13:21.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Move! You there, stand aside!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.69,0:13:24.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calling from 20336, business area level 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.22,0:13:34.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It might be 1/6 G here, but a person still isn't light...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.25,0:13:37.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Especially one who's wearing a spacesuit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.26,0:13:43.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've come to, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.82,0:13:44.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.15,0:13:49.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The lunar surface. We escaped from the Von Braun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.74,0:13:54.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The capsule's transmitter broke when we landed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.28,0:13:58.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and there's no telling the SOS signals from our spacesuits are getting through.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.31,0:14:03.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But there's a manned communications facility\N40km to the north at Kepler Crater.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.64,0:14:09.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we keep going at an average pace of 4.5km an hour without resting,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.22,0:14:12.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...we'll get there before our oxygen runs out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.62,0:14:15.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,4.5km an hour? For nearly ten hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.27,0:14:20.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was outside for 12 hours once when we were collecting debris in a polar resonance orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.37,0:14:21.33,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:26.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.45,0:14:29.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the same as space, where you're just floating around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.63,0:14:32.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have to factor in the gravity here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.72,0:14:34.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but it's only 1/6 G.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.23,0:14:37.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! The impact on your legs is still the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:43.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,4.5km an hour for ten hours?\NWith me on your back? That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.18,0:14:48.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty light, Claire. You'll have to give me your dieting secrets sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.22,0:14:54.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be okay.\NSenpai worked me really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.32,0:14:58.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to when I lived on Earth,\NI'm a lot stronger now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.40,0:15:01.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of people get weaker when they come into space, but not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.97,0:15:03.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm proud of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.48,0:15:10.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No sign of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:11.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri! Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.33,0:15:18.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're one of Tanabe's friends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.52,0:15:21.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe was with you, wasn't she?\NWhere is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.79,0:15:22.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is she being treated for injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.02,0:15:25.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.15,0:15:28.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know?\NWait, don't tell me that you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.79,0:15:33.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't leave her behind!\NI had to concentrate on getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.99,0:15:38.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Two more hours...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.60,0:15:41.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't think about it.\NKeep those legs moving...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.78,0:15:49.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My knees...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.84,0:15:55.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't I see it?\NWhere's Kepler Crater?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:15:59.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Put me down...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.71,0:16:01.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Put me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:06.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you in pain?\NJust bear with it a while longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.49,0:16:08.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you to put me down and go on without me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.18,0:16:14.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?\NIf you stayed out here, you'd die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.08,0:16:16.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.92,0:16:19.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to die here, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.19,0:16:23.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's too early to give up.\NThat kind of talk isn't like you, Claire-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.85,0:16:28.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't given up.\NI've been prepared to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.99,0:16:30.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I agreed to\NHakim's invitation to join him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.43,0:16:32.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.07,0:16:37.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I coached the Space Defense Front and helped them steal the Toy Box.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.58,0:16:40.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The plan was to drop the Von Braun onto Sea of Tranquility City.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.43,0:16:43.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.47,0:16:47.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... a terrorist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.90,0:16:51.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Quit trying to test me, okay?\NI won't fall for lies like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.39,0:16:53.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then what was\NI doing there on the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.26,0:16:58.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fee-san and Yuri-san and Hachi, they were all there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.88,0:17:03.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how many lunar residents and Technora employees we killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.34,0:17:07.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Serves them right! That's what they get for abandoning me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.24,0:17:12.29,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead, put me down and leave me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.48,0:17:16.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I killed all of the people you care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.83,0:17:20.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a worthless human being.\NI don't deserve to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.29,0:17:23.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that. There's no...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.41,0:17:24.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no love in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.01,0:17:27.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't save anything with love.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.89,0:17:30.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true at all.\NIf you have love, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.39,0:17:33.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then use that love of yours to save us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.52,0:17:37.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Will love bring a rescue team?\NWill it call up extra air?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.33,0:17:40.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Will it bring Hachi and the others back to life?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.16,0:17:44.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe that you're a terrorist, Claire-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.73,0:17:48.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or that you killed Fee-san and Yuri-san and Senpai, so cut it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.76,0:17:52.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't believe for an instant that there's a human being in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.53,0:17:53.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...whose life is worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.53,0:17:58.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Every single life is precious.\NEvery one of them should be cherished!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.23,0:18:01.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But here you are, talking about how one life is valuable, while another isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.36,0:18:04.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make any sense to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.71,0:18:14.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you've committed crimes, then don't die!\NStay alive and repay your debt!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.64,0:18:19.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All you need is love... Love can...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:23.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and your love again...\NYour "love" is shallow and meaningless!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.19,0:18:26.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Has this "love" of yours ever saved even a single person's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.34,0:18:29.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk to me about love if you can't back it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.00,0:18:32.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not all talk. I'm gonna...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.52,0:18:36.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know, it's not too late. Why don't you try to become a nun or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.55,0:18:38.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that kind of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.49,0:18:41.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My love is...\NIt's something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.47,0:18:44.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, you're just one of the fortunate few.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.42,0:18:48.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been lucky, not by a long shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.72,0:18:51.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's when people haven't been blessed that they need love the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.43,0:18:54.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once you have love, you see things differently!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.80,0:18:59.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, it won't! A pathetic, worthless life is all that's waiting for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.85,0:19:02.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If I didn't, do you think that the miserable people would suddenly become happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.83,0:19:06.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You said you loved me! Were our marriage vows nothing but lies?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:08.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you have love...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.84,0:19:12.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's embarrassing to say it, but we're all unemployed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.49,0:19:18.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My wife used to act as our kunoichi.\NNo, I suppose she isn't my wife anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.49,0:19:20.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you have love...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.46,0:19:22.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.31,0:19:26.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This kind of thing happens a lot when you're out in space a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.04,0:19:34.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you have...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.25,0:19:37.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I love him, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.87,0:19:39.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.34,0:19:41.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You'll figure it out soon enough, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:43.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you say you're gonna make your dreams come true,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.14,0:19:46.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...there's some things you can do and some things you can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.61,0:19:48.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.70,0:19:52.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter what I write.\NOnce I'm dead, it's all over for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.76,0:19:53.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no love in that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.98,0:19:57.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As if something like that could ever create peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.94,0:20:01.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It will! If people love the world and each other, it will!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.83,0:20:04.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have my own life.\NAnd you have your own, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.27,0:20:06.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How can you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.37,0:20:11.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All the loneliness! All the pain!\NAll the doubts! All the regrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.99,0:20:15.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't deserve them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.99,0:20:18.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,268)}No way in hell am I gonna give 'em away to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.94,0:20:22.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong! I know that you're wrong, Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.24,0:20:24.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If there's love, people will...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.44,0:20:35.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm such an idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.40,0:20:40.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't the one who saved Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.12,0:20:44.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What saved him was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.41,0:20:52.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The thing that Senpai is in love with isn't me, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.84,0:21:03.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't me that he's in love with...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.21,0:21:12.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Will it be much longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.20,0:21:19.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We should be sending out an SOS, and no matter how weak the signal is, it ought to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.86,0:21:24.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What? My oxygen is low?\NIt's sooner than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.59,0:21:26.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! Do I have a leak?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.69,0:21:35.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Five more minutes?\NBut I still have 10km to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.00,0:21:39.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My air...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.25,0:21:42.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody, respond! Help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.32,0:21:45.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost out of oxygen! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.70,0:21:48.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?\NI'm down to three minutes now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.63,0:21:52.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, talk to me! You copy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.19,0:21:54.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How can this be happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.61,0:21:57.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, we're gonna...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.18,0:22:02.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire-san should still have some...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.12,0:22:06.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to die here anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.09,0:22:12.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you to put me down and go on without me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.53,0:22:18.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't given up.\NI've been prepared to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.30,0:22:25.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I killed all of the people you care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.74,0:22:29.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a worthless human being.\NI don't deserve to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.61,0:22:35.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't deserve to live...
